description:
secretx-core/src/lib.rs:1295: SigningAlgorithm derives Debug but not Display. Users who hit a key-type-mismatch error path (see crate-secretsx-0gzu in the broader epic backlog) will see Debug output ('EcdsaP256Sha256') in error messages — which is fine, but error messages built with format!("{algorithm}") need the type to impl Display.

Idiomatic Rust: any user-visible type (an algorithm name in an error message is user-visible) should impl Display, distinct from Debug. The Debug output is the developer's representation; the Display output is the operator's.

Fix:
    impl std::fmt::Display for SigningAlgorithm {
        fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
            f.write_str(match self {
                Self::Ed25519 => "Ed25519",
                Self::EcdsaP256Sha256 => "ECDSA P-256 / SHA-256",
                Self::RsaPss2048Sha256 => "RSA-PSS 2048 / SHA-256",
            })
        }
    }
The exact strings should match what shows up in PKCS#8 OID human names so logs are searchable.
